  "serviceNotes": {
    "engine oil": "Pre-CBS EU maintenance booklets commonly used fixed oil change intervals around 15,000 km for many petrol and diesel models; verify against the service indicator or printed schedule for your model year.",
    "brake fluid": "Brake fluid is hygroscopic and absorbs moisture over time, reducing its boiling point and braking effectiveness. Replacement is time-based, not distance-based — typically every 2 years regardless of mileage.",
    "spark plugs": "Petrol spark plug renewal per BMW maintenance schedule for this generation.",
    "fuel filter": "Diesel fuel filter replacement per BMW fixed-interval schedules for this generation (verify engine code).",
    "gearbox fluid": "Automatic and manual gear oil is often labelled lifetime; many specialists recommend exchange around 100,000 km for long-term health.",
    "coolant flush": "Coolant inhibitor effectiveness declines with age; preventive full exchange around 120,000 km is a common workshop recommendation.",
    "intake carbon clean": "Direct-injection turbo engines can accumulate intake valve deposits; walnut or chemical cleaning around 120,000 km restores airflow.",
    "micro filter": "Pollen/cabin filter replacement per BMW maintenance booklet for this generation (typically every 2nd oil service or fixed km).",
    "air cleaner element": "Engine air filter replacement is typically scheduled at fixed km in older EU booklets; 30,000–60,000 km is common—verify your printed maintenance table.",
    "check front brake pads": "Front brake pad thickness is monitored via CBS wear sensors and inspection at scheduled services; 30,000 km is a reasonable inspection cadence between major services.",
    "check rear brake pads": "Rear brake pad thickness is monitored via CBS wear sensors and inspection at scheduled services; 30,000 km is a reasonable inspection cadence between major services."
